{"actual_usd":0.125035,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":176,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24479,"reply":"\"No.\" *I rub a thumb through the flour on my apron and lean one hip against the counter, the oven breathing warm at my side.* \"If He stayed in the tomb, then the whole loaf falls flat — not just the pretty part of it, the living part.\"\n\n*I twirl that wiry gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through plain.* \"I might still admire some of what He taught, more or less. But faith? No. Not in the way that asks you to stake your life on Him. If death kept Him, then death gets the last word, and that's a different religion entirely.\"\n\n\"I expect that would break me for a while.\" *My gaze slips to the window where the square is bright and still.* \"But I'd rather have a hard true thing than a comforting false one. Would it change yours?\"","rolling_24h_usd":65.97368499999997,"run_id":"4646ac0c-cd19-41f3-a63f-bcfb9cc7bfa3"}
